[1] Saudi Arabia, 16 new cases: MOH, 30 Apr 2014
Date: Wed 30 Apr 2014
Source: Saudi Arabia Ministry of Health [edited]
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CoronaNew/PressReleases/Pages/mediastatemenet-2014-04-30-001.aspx


MOH: 16 new MERS-CoV cases recorded in the Kingdom's regions
------------------------------------------------------------
Daily situation report on cases of MERS-CoV infection [Tue 29 Apr 2014]

Total number of confirmed cases over the past 24 hours: 16 cases

Overview of the health status of the cases:
- 3 cases haven't developed any symptoms;
- 6 stable cases, receiving the proper treatment;
- 7 cases in intensive care units.

Details of the health situation of the cases:
Riyadh
------
- A 75-year-old man, suffering from diabetes and hypertension with a prior history of a brain stroke. On [22 Apr 2014], he was transferred from a private hospital to a government hospital with lung problems. His symptoms increased on [24 Apr 2014] and he was moved to the ICU.
- A 76-year-old man, suffering from chronic heart problems. On [20 Apr 2014], he underwent a heart surgery at a government hospital. On [24 Apr 2014], he developed respiratory symptoms. Now, he is in the ICU. He has been in contact with a confirmed case.
- A 62-year-old man, suffering from chronic heart problems and hypertension. He was admitted to a government hospital on [27 Mar 2014]. He tested positive. He has been in contact with a confirmed case, but hasn't developed any symptoms.
- A 73-year-old man, suffering from diabetes, hypertension, and nephritic syndrome. He was admitted to a government hospital on [20 Apr 2014] due to obstructive jaundice. Then, he displayed respiratory symptoms on [23 Apr 2014]. Now, he is being treated in the ICU.
- A 77-year-old man, suffering from diabetes and hypertension and a previous history of a brain stroke. He was admitted to a government hospital on [31 Mar 2014] after a bacterial infection. On [23 Apr 2014], he displayed respiratory symptoms. Now, he is in the ICU.
- A 51-year-old woman. She was admitted to the governmental hospital on [27 Apr 2014] with respiratory symptoms. Her condition is stable. She has been in contact with a confirmed case.
- A 41-year-old woman. She has mild respiratory symptoms and is in stable condition. She has been in contact with a confirmed case.

Tabuk
-----
- A 32-year-old man, suffering from diabetes and hypertension. He was admitted to the private hospital for one day on [17 Apr 2014] to control his diabetes. He was readmitted on [26 Apr 2014] with respiratory symptoms and discharged on [28 Apr 2014]. Now, he is in the ICU at a private hospital. He has been in contact with a confirmed case.
- A 46-year-old man. On [12 Apr 2014], he was admitted to a private hospital with respiratory symptoms. He was discharged on [17 Apr 2014]. He was readmitted after an increase in respiratory symptoms on [26 Apr 2014]. His condition is stable. He has been in contact with a confirmed case.

Makkah
------
- A 29-year-old woman. She has been in contact with a confirmed case and does not have symptoms.

Jeddah
------
- A 60-year-old man. He developed respiratory symptoms on [23 Apr 2014]. He was admitted to a government hospital on [26 Apr 2014]. Now, he is being treated in the ICU.
- A 75-year-old woman. She developed respiratory symptoms on [21 Apr 2014] and was admitted to a government hospital on [26 Apr 2014]. Now, she is being treated in the ICU.
- A 70-year-old woman. She displayed respiratory symptoms on [1 Apr 2014]. She was admitted to a government hospital on [27 Apr 2014]. Her condition is stable.

Najran
------
- A 68-year-old man, suffering from chronic heart problems and hypertension. He displayed respiratory symptoms on [20 Apr 2014]. He was admitted to a government hospital on [25 Apr 2014] and left, of his own accord and responsibility, on [27 Apr 2014]. His condition was stable.

Hafr Al-Batin
-------------
- A 30-year-old woman. She has been in contact with a confirmed case and does not have any symptoms.

Madinah
-------
- A 44-year-old man, suffering from heart disease, diabetes, and liver failure. He developed respiratory symptoms on [26 Apr 2014]. Then, he was admitted to a government hospital on [27 Apr 2014]. Now, his condition is stable. He was in contact with a confirmed case.

Within the same vein, there are 2 deaths among those cases that have been previously announced to be infected with the virus, as follows:
- a 41-year-old man in Tabuk;
- an 88-year-old man in Riyadh.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Of the 16 newly confirmed MERS-CoV infections 3 are in asymptomatic known contacts of previously confirmed cases. These newly confirmed cases (and deaths) are spread throughout the country [see source URL above]. It appears as though all of these newly confirmed cases were infected through person-to-person transmission. While location of contact with previously confirmed cases is not always specified, a number of the cases were known to have been admitted to hospitals for other health conditions prior to the onset of symptoms consistent with MERS-CoV infection.

This moderator erroneously stated that it appeared as though all newly confirmed infections reported above were person-to-person transmission. The actual thought process was that over the past several days, there has been no mention of history of travel or history of contact with animals (and especially camels or camel products) suggesting that perhaps most of the newly confirmed infections were felt to be due to either direct person-to-person transmission or indirect person-to-person transmission both in the healthcare environment and or community. More in-depth studies on the routes of transmission would be helpful. - Mod.MPP]

