[2] Saudi Arabia, 6 new cases: MOH, 29 Apr 2014
Date: Tue 29 Apr 2014
Source: Saudi Arabia Ministry of Health [edited]
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CoronaNew/PressReleases/Pages/mediastatemenet-2014-04-29-001.aspx


MOH: 6 new MERS-CoV cases recorded in the Kingdom's regions
------------------------------------------------------------
Daily situation report on cases of MERS-CoV infection [Mon 28 Apr 2014]

Overview of the health status of the cases:
- 4 cases haven't developed any symptoms.
- 2 stable hospitalized cases, receiving proper treatment.

Details of new cases today [28 Apr 2014]:
Riyadh
------
- A 65-year-old woman, suffering from several chronic diseases. She was admitted to a government hospital several months ago and remains hospitalized. She has been in contact with a confirmed case, but hasn't developed any symptoms.

Jeddah
------
- A 42-year-old man who developed respiratory symptoms on [22 Apr 2014]. Then, he was admitted to a private hospital on [23 Apr 2014]. Now, his health status is stable. He has been in contact with a confirmed case.
- A 38-year-old woman. She has been in contact with a confirmed case, but he hasn't developed any symptoms.
- A 28-year-old man, suffering from nephritic syndrome. He developed respiratory symptoms on [23 Apr 2014]. On [25 Apr 2014], he was admitted to a government hospital. Now, his health status is stable.

Tabuk
-----
- A 39-year-old man, suffering from chronic heart problems and asthma. On [14 Apr 2014], he was admitted to a private hospital. He had shortness of breath and admitted to ICU. He was discharged on [18 Apr 2014] and readmitted on [23 Apr 2014] with shortness of breath and fever. He was diagnosed with lung infection and again was discharged on [25 Apr 2014]. Reports show he has been in contact with a confirmed case.

Makkah
------
- An 18 year old woman. She has been in contact with a confirmed case, but hasn't developed any symptoms.

Furthermore, 3 deaths have been reported among cases that have been previously announced:
- a 79-year-old man in Riyadh;
- a 61-year-old man in Riyadh;
- a 56-year-old man in Riyadh.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Of the 6 newly reported laboratory confirmed infections with the MERS-CoV, 4 were in asymptomatic contacts. - Mod.MPP]

